\section{How GDAL resolves a configuration option}{

For a given key, GDAL checks, in order: a thread-local option, the process-global in-memory
option (set via \code{CPLSetConfigOption()}; this also holds values loaded from the
\link[=gdal_config_file]{GDAL config file} at initialization), an environment variable of the same
name (read live via \code{getenv()}), and finally the built-in default. Two consequences drive this
API's design:
\itemize{
\item \strong{Set is authoritative}: a value applied with \code{gdal_config_set()} wins over an environment
variable for as long as it is set.
\item \strong{Unset is not}: clearing the in-memory option (what \code{set_config_option(key, "")} does)
merely \emph{reveals} the environment variable underneath again. You cannot force GDAL's built-in
default while an envvar exists - hence the explicit \code{mode} argument of \code{gdal_config_unset()}
(\code{"reveal"}, \code{"mask"}, or \code{"scrub"}).
}

Because environment variables, other packages, and the config file all write to the same GDAL
state, the package never mirrors values: reads always go to GDAL, and the package only records
the \emph{deltas} it applied (plus what was effective beforehand, for restore).
}

\section{Known options}{

Advisory typo checking (classed warning, never blocking - custom application-defined options
are legal) draws on: GDAL's compile-time known-option registry (\code{\link[=gdal_known_config_opts]{gdal_known_config_opts()}},
parsed from the version-pinned GDAL source header), the VSI/network/credential
options enumerated from the running GDAL build (\code{\link[gdalraster:vsi_get_fs_options]{gdalraster::vsi_get_fs_options()}} across all
registered filesystems), the curated per-driver configuration options (driver metadata table),
and GDAL-relevant environment variables present at load. Keys GDAL already resolves to a value
are never flagged, and a key found in none of the lists is confirmed against the running build
itself via \code{\link[=gdal_config_option_known]{gdal_config_option_known()}} (GDAL >= 3.11) before a warning is raised.
}

